observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management require the - 

a.	Inventory Committee to strictly conduct physical inventory of PPE annually and semestral for Supplies and submit the required reports within the prescribed deadline; 



b.	GSO-Designate to update the property records based on the result of physical inventory and reconcile the same with accounting records to make the records reflective of the actual count of PPEs;



c.	undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular No. 2020-006 to come up with reliable balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability; and

d.	Municipal Accountant and GSO–Designate to maintain the PPE ledger cards and Property Cards, respectively, for each item of the PPE.

We recommend that the Management -
enforce the mandatory issuance of certificate of occupancy prior to the use or occupancy of a completed structure;
require the OBO to provide status of the issued building permits without certificates of occupancy and impose the appropriate fees for completed structures;
tap the barangay officials to regularly report to the OBO of the on-going construction and completed structures in their barangays in order for the OBO to facilitate monitoring compliance of structures;
establish a formal coordination and data-sharing mechanism between the OBO and OMA to monitor the status of construction activities and ensure timely property assessments; and
conduct a comprehensive review of all the issued building permits and identify completed structures that have not been assessed for real property tax and require the OMA to update tax assessment roll accordingly.

1.6  We recommended and Management agreed to -
require the Inventory Committee to strictly conduct physical inventory of PPE annually and semestral for Supplies and submit the required reports within the prescribed deadline;
require the GSO-Designate to update the property records based on the result of physical inventory and reconcile the same with accounting records to make the records reflective of the actual count of PPEs;
undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular No. 2020-006 to come up with reliable balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability; and
direct the Municipal Accountant and GSO–Designate to maintain the PPE ledger cards and Property Cards, respectively, for each item of the PPE.
